title: Corban McGregor
text:
Corban Baxter ("<a href="n%C3%A9e">née</a>" McGregor; born 10 April 1994) is an Australian international <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer who captains the <a href="Sydney%20Roosters">Sydney Roosters</a> in the <a href="NRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">NRL Women's Premiership</a> and the <a href="Cronulla-Sutherland%20Sharks">Cronulla-Sutherland Sharks</a> in the <a href="NSWRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">NSWRL Women's Premiership</a>. 
A , or , she is an <a href="Australian%20Jillaroos">Australia</a> and <a href="New%20South%20Wales%20women%27s%20rugby%20league%20team">New South Wales</a> representative.
Background.
McGregor was born in <a href="Auckland">Auckland</a>, New Zealand, and has <a href="M%C4%81ori%20people">Māori</a> ancestry. She moved to Australia with her family at the age of 3.
Playing career.
In 2015, McGregor began playing <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> for the <a href="Helensburgh%20Tigers">Helensburgh Tigers</a>. That year, she made her debut for <a href="New%20South%20Wales%20women%27s%20rugby%20league%20team">New South Wales</a> in a 4-all draw with <a href="Queensland%20women%27s%20rugby%20league%20team">Queensland</a>.
On 6 May 2016, she made her Test debut for <a href="Australian%20Jillaroos">Australia</a>, starting at in a 16–26 loss to <a href="Kiwi%20Ferns">New Zealand</a>.
On 2 December 2017, McGregor started at in Australia's 23–16 <a href="2017%20Women%27s%20Rugby%20League%20World%20Cup%20Final">2017 Women's Rugby League World Cup Final</a> win over New Zealand.
In June 2018, she represented NSW City at the Women's National Championships. On 17 June 2018, she signed for the <a href="Sydney%20Roosters">Sydney Roosters</a> <a href="NRL%20Women%27s%20Premiership">NRL Women's Premiership</a> team. On 22 June 2018, during the inaugural <a href="Women%27s%20State%20of%20Origin">Women's State of Origin</a>, McGregor suffered a shoulder injury, ruling her out of the entire <a href="2018%20NRL%20Women%27s%20season">2018 NRL Women's season</a>.
In Round 1 of the <a href="2019%20NRL%20Women%27s%20season">2019 NRL Women's season</a>, McGregor made her debut for the Roosters in their 12–16 loss to the <a href="New%20Zealand%20Warriors">New Zealand Warriors</a>. In October 2019, she represented Australia at the <a href="2019%20Rugby%20League%20World%20Cup%209s">2019 Rugby League World Cup 9s</a>, where they lost to New Zealand in the finals.
On 22 February 2020, she represented the <a href="M%C4%81ori%20All%20Stars">Māori All Stars</a> in their 4–10 loss to the Indigenous All Stars.
On 25 October 2020, she started at and captained the Roosters' in their 10–20 <a href="2020%20NRL%20Grand%20Final">Grand Final</a> loss to the <a href="Brisbane%20Broncos">Brisbane Broncos</a>. 
On 20 February 2021, she captained the <a href="New%20Zealand%20M%C4%81ori%20rugby%20league%20team">Māori All Stars</a> in their 24–0 win over the <a href="Indigenous%20All%20Stars%20%28rugby%20league%29">Indigenous All Stars</a>.
